    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i'm also seeing some feedback from clients about \"pilling\" and the fabric feeling less \"impenetrable\" to heavy moisture or wear. if we really dial up the thread density to the absolute max to create a tighter, more protective barrier for the fibers, is there a point of diminishing returns where the weave becomes too tight to be functional?",
