      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, there is a distinct point of diminishing returns when pushing thread density to its absolute maximum. Over-tightening the weave can lead to excessive stiffness, reduced drape, and increased handling stress, which itself can induce premature fiber damage. Extremely dense weaves can also trap moisture within the structure, potentially leading to mold issues rather than preventing penetration. You must find the optimal density balance between protective barrier strength and desired textile hand-feel.",
